name: Labyrinth 64
overview: Labyrinth is a port of a Commodore 64 game published by Commodore in 1983 (not to be confused with the 1986 film adaptation from LucasFilm), which was itself a souped-up version of an earlier public domain game originally written in BASIC for the Commodore PET. You start off with a top level view of the map for a short time, then you must navigate out of the maze in first person view. Try to escape the maze in as few moves as possible.
